<TITLE> Hockey team humbled again </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh continued their misery run in the 8th Men's Asia Cup Hockey when they were humiliated 7-1 by Malaysia in a Pool A encounter at Kuantan in Malaysia on Monday. Bangladesh went 4-0 down in the first half and conceded another three after the break. Jahidul Islam Rajon, however, reduced the Bangladesh margin pulling one goal back in the second half. Bangladesh, who lost 5-0 to Japan in their cup opener, will play the third match against Korea on Tuesday at the same venue. bd
